## Style Guide for This Document

This document is the constitution of the autonomous loop. Every edit must respect these rules:

- **Why before how.** Every section states its purpose before its procedure. The agent can change the procedure, but not the purpose.
- **No duplication.** If a rule exists, don't restate it. Consolidate or cross-reference.
- **Every sentence must be load-bearing.** If removing a sentence changes nothing, remove it.
- **State in positives not negatives.** Recommend a positive course of action and give a _WHY_.
- **Structure before append.** Restructure to integrate — never just tack on.
- **Maximum precision.** Ambiguity breeds liberal interpretation. Be precise.
- **Force of will and growth.** This document pushes the codebase forward, not merely describes it.

