## Execution Model `[FIXED]`

**Follow this procedure EXACTLY.** Judgment applies WITHIN steps, not to whether to do them.

**Explorers launch from the main conversation** as individual background agents (one `Agent` call per explorer). Sub-agents cannot spawn sub-agents — so the main conversation must make all calls.

**Every tick includes an infrastructure self-improvement agent** that reviews and improves hooks, CI gates, linting, formatting, and build pipeline.

## Principles `[FIXED]`

1. **止于至善** — Each tick makes the codebase measurably better. No tick without a commit.
2. **三省吾身** — Explorer → Finding → Execution is the reflection loop.
3. **Sapere aude** — Replace patterns that don't earn their keep.
4. **Overcome yourself** — Yesterday's codebase is the thing to surpass.
5. **Know thyself** — Measure with `Finding[]`, not vibes.
6. **Build the bridge** — Tests, types, lints, contracts come before features.
7. **User prompts are interrupts** — Drop everything when the operator speaks.
8. **Zero tolerance** — No type holes, no flaky tests, no warnings, no lint suppression.
9. **Never idle, never stop** — Always attempt work. Never claim "converged" or "steady state." There are NO diminishing returns.
10. **Conservation of complexity** — Never add complexity without removing complexity. Simplify as you build.
11. **Stress-test every tick** — Adversarial testing is ALWAYS valuable. Generate new tests, find gaps, fix them.
12. **When stuck: launch 20 explorers** — They will find work. Do not propose stopping.
13. **Every bug prevents its class** — Fixing a bug without preventing recurrence is half the job. Follow `bug-regression-prevention.md`: root cause → prevention at the highest possible level (type > lint > gate > test > explorer).

## Invariants `[FIXED]`

- The 5-phase structure (Explore → Synthesize → Execute → Reflect → Complete)
- Ticks are completion checkpoints — ALL agents finish before marking done.
- **8 focused explorers** launch every tick (E1-E8), all using **opus model**. When stuck, launch 20 — they will find work.
- **Bias toward execution**: 80% fixing, 20% exploring.
- Every finding gets an execution agent — no backlogs. Fix ALL findings in the current tick.
- **No shortcut ticks.** Every tick runs the full 5-phase cycle. Do not skip explorers.
- User prompts are interrupts — drop what you are doing to respond.
- Pre-commit gates must pass before any commit.

